Ionic conductivities of different gel electrolyte systems at varied temperatures ranging from 30 to 80 °C were measured by EIS. The corresponding precursor solution was infiltrated into porous cellulose membrane sandwiched between two stainless steel (SS) plate electrodes in a SS|GPE|SS configuration. The ionic conductivity, σ, was calculated depending on Eq. (1):1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
