				\begin{document}$$\upsigma =\frac{L}{RS}$$\end{document}σ=LRSwhere L is the thickness of the GPE electrolyte, S is the contact area between GPEs and SS electrode and R is the resistance measured from EIS in the frequency ranging from 0.1 Hz to 10 MHz with an AC amplitude of 10 mV. To investigate the temperature-dependent ionic conductivity for GPEs, the activation energy (Ea) was evaluated according to Arrhenius Eq. (2):2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
