				\begin{document}$${\sigma }_{T}=A{e}^{\frac{{-E}_{a}}{{k}_{B}T}}$$\end{document}σT=Ae-EakBTwhere A is a pre-exponential factor, Ea is activation energy, kB is the Boltzmann constant and T is the absolute temperature. The Li+ transference number, tLi+, was determined by a combined method of chronoamperometry and AC impedance spectroscopy with a Li||Li symmetric cell, according to Eq. (3):3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
